15 March 2022 South Africa will host its fourth SAIC on Thursday, 24 March 2022, at the Sandton Convention Centre in Johannesburg. Members of the media are informed that the media registration is now closed. No applications will be accepted at this stage. The following accreditation process will apply: Dates The live accreditation centre will be dedicated to the media members from Saturday, 19, and Sunday, 20 March 2022 from 08h30- 17h30. Media are urged to collect their accreditation in person on these dates. Venue Accreditation venus is at the IDC Auditorium, 82 Grayston Drive, Sandton. Requirements The accreditation system is live, which means the media must physically present themselves to collect their accreditation. Required Documents for Live Accreditation: Important South African Investment Conference media event Members of the media are invited to the South African Investment Conference Press Workshop to discuss media arrangements and the programme of the Investment Conference. Date:Â  Tuesday, 22 March 2022 Time: 14h00 - 15h30Venue: The Sandton Convention Centre - Bill Gallagher Room Please RSVP to zeenat@gcis.gov.za Media enquiries:Ayanda HollowOverall Media LiaisonEmail: holo@gcis.gov.zaCell: 061 488 0634 Mmemme Mogotsi Accreditation and Media EventsE-mail: mmemme@gcis.gov.zaCell: 072 856 4288 We look forward to welcoming you to the South Africa Investment Conference 2022.